  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "As with SMC 2, the most computationally expensive step of the NEnKF algorithm is the resamplemove step; if executed at time t, the cost is O(tM N).",
    "We, therefore, aim to avoid expensive calculation of the likelihood p (θ) enkf,t (y 0:t |x 1:N 0:t) for proposed parameter values that are likely to be rejected.",
    "Hence, we propose to replace the standard Metropolis-Hastings move in step 3 of Algorithm 6 with a delayed acceptance (DA) move (e.g.",
    "Christen and Fox, 2005; Golightly et al., 2015; Banterle et al., 2019).",
    "The DA move requires a surrogate for which we use the (unique) resampled particles and their corresponding log-likelihood evaluations."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Christen and Fox, 2005; Golightly et al., 2015; Banterle et al., 2019)."
  ]
}